  "text": "At the same time, however, the tension with privacy around the tracking of very personal, intimate employee activity remains an ever-present issue. Often, the topic is approached in terms of personalized medicine and fitness benefits for millions of users of popular apps and devices. However, a lot of support is generally needed to help users understand devices and what standards of data quality are (or are not) being adhered to by big-name brand devices, such as FitBit, Jawbone and Nike Fuelband [CITATION_1] .",
